3-Managing local users and groups
User Managment List,Create,Modify,Remove User Account
user account
1- User login name
2- Password
3- User ID root 0 - users 1000 , 1001 .... UID 1-999 reserved local system Accounts
4- Primary Group default system will create Group same as user name ali ali
5- Home directory user profile default location /home/username user root /root
6- Default shell default shell for users bash
## list users
/etc/passwd store all user's informations
/etc/shadow store all user's passwords encrypted
# id username
root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash
hany1:x:1001:1001::/home/hany1:/bin/bash
username:x:UserID:PrimaryGroupID:Comment:HomeDirectory:DefaultShell
## Create Users
# useradd hany2 create user with default settings
# useradd -s /bin/ksh -u 1010 -c "sales manager" hany10 create user with custom settings
# passwd hany1 set user password
# id hany1
uid=1001(hany1) gid=1001(hany1) groups=1001(hany1)
## modify user settings
usermod option username
# usermod -u 1009 hany10
# usermod -c "hr manager" hany10
# usermod -s /bin/bash hany10
## Remove user
userdel username delete user only
userdel -r username delete user and home directory
## switch user
# su - hany1 switch to hany1
$ pwd view current login user
/home/hany
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Group Managment permission - mail
List , create ,Modify Group Members and remove Group
User primary Group Default , Secondary Groups
# vi /etc/group list all groups
## Create Group
# groupadd sales
# groupadd it
# groupadd hr
# groupadd managers
## modify Group members
# usermod -g sales ali set primary Group to sales
# usermod -G it ali set secondary Group
# usermod -aG it ali add Secondary Group
# id ali
uid=1002(ali) gid=1004(sales) groups=1004(sales),1005(it),1006(hr)
# groupdel it remove group
# groupdel sales
groupdel: cannot remove the primary group of user 'ali' can not remove primary group for user
